# Operators in Java

DSA-003A

### Types of Operators in Java

---

### üß† What are Operators?

> Operators are special symbols used to perform operations on variables and values.
> 
> 
> Example: `+`, `-`, `==`, `&&`, etc.
> 

---

### üî¢ Type of Operators

| #Ô∏è‚É£ | Operator Type | Use (in short) |
| --- | --- | --- |
| 1Ô∏è‚É£ | Arithmetic Operators | Basic math: `+`, `-`, `*`, `/`, `%` |
| 2Ô∏è‚É£ | Unary Operators | One operand: `++`, `--`, `+`, `-`, `!` |
| 3Ô∏è‚É£ | Relational Operators | Comparison: `==`, `!=`, `<`, `>`, etc. |
| 4Ô∏è‚É£ | Logical Operators | Boolean logic: `&&`, ` |
| 5Ô∏è‚É£ | Assignment Operators | Assign value: `=`, `+=`, `-=`, etc. |
| 6Ô∏è‚É£ | Bitwise Operators | Bit-level ops: `&`, ` |
| 7Ô∏è‚É£ | Ternary Operator | Short if-else: `condition ? a : b` |
| 8Ô∏è‚É£ | instanceof Operator | Object check: `obj instanceof Class` |

---

### üß† 1-Line Trick to Remember:

> 
> 
> 
> ‚Üí `A`rithmetic, `U`nary, `R`elational, `L`ogical, `A`ssignment, `T`ernary, `B`itwise, `I`nstanceof
> 

## **Most Used Operators**

---

### 1Ô∏è‚É£ **Arithmetic Operator**

**Use**: Basic math operations (add, subtract, multiply, divide, remainder).

**Example**:

```java
int a = 10, b = 5;
System.out.println(a + b); // Output: 15
```

---

### 2Ô∏è‚É£ **Unary Operator**

**Use**: Works on a single value (increase, decrease, reverse boolean).

**Example**:

```java
int a = 5;
System.out.println(++a);  // Output: 6 (Pre-increment)
```

---

### 3Ô∏è‚É£ **Relational Operator**

**Use**: Compares two values (>, <, >=, <=, ==, !=) ‚Üí gives true/false.

**Example**:

```java
int a = 5, b = 10;
System.out.println(a < b); // Output: true
```

---

### 4Ô∏è‚É£ **Logical Operator**

**Use**: Combines multiple conditions ‚Üí gives true/false.

**Operators**: `&&` (AND), `||` (OR), `!` (NOT)

**Example**:

```java
int age = 20;
System.out.println(age > 18 && age < 30); // true
```

---

### 5Ô∏è‚É£ **Assignment Operator**

**Use**: Assigns or updates values of variables.

**Example**:

```java
int a = 10;
a += 5;  // same as a = a + 5; ‚Üí a becomes 15
```

---

## üß† Interview Cracker Trick:

| Operator | Meaning | Trick To Remember |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Arithmetic | Math | Add, Subtract, Multiply |
| Unary | 1 variable | ++, --, ! (single value change) |
| Relational | Compare | Always returns true/false |
| Logical | Combine checks | `if(condition1 && condition2)` etc. |
| Assignment | Set value | `=`, `+=`, `-=`, etc. |

